WEBVTT

00:02.528 --> 00:18.383
Following the hearings on the Laredo Transfer 
Bill in the House Higher Education Committee, it

00:02.528 --> 00:18.383
was pretty obvious that the bill was not going 
anywhere as far as the Higher Education Committee

00:02.528 --> 00:18.383
was concerned. However, procedurally, there is a 
way to bypass the committee. Would the Senate

00:27.552 --> 00:32.417
amend a House bill and it be sent back to the House 
for concurrence, then the bill would not be going

00:33.427 --> 00:42.317
through committee. It would have to be a bill that 
would be ruled as germane. So we immediately set

00:48.944 --> 00:57.493
out to determine how many bills there might be that 
were germane or could be ruled germane. to the

00:58.503 --> 01:05.676
subject of transfer of Laredo from A&M system to 
the University of Texas system. One bill in

01:07.279 --> 01:14.352
particular that was germane was legislation that 
would transfer the Baylor College of Dentistry

01:15.800 --> 01:21.168
into the Texas A&M University system. This bill 
was out of committee in the Senate and was

01:22.109 --> 01:35.348
scheduled

01:22.109 --> 01:35.348
for debate on the Senate floor.

01:38.352 --> 01:45.402
Fortunately, the supporters of the Baylor 
College of Dentistry in Dallas became aware of the

01:45.938 --> 01:58.340
problem that could exist should their bill be 
amended and began to lobby to see that it was not

01:45.938 --> 01:58.340
amended. I understand that the Lieutenant 
Governor took the position that the Baylor

01:58.360 --> 02:08.959
College of Dentistry bill would not be amended. 
and later took the position that no amendments to

02:09.563 --> 02:22.002
transfer Laredo would be allowed on any of the 
bills as far as he was personally concerned.

02:25.568 --> 02:37.967
This was fortunate because I think that the 
transfer of Laredo would have been viewed as a

02:25.568 --> 02:37.967
weakness on the part of the Texas A&M University 
system to allow this to happen. and would have

02:38.690 --> 02:43.134
given the NM system a black eye for years to come. We 
gained a position of some strength and the

02:45.176 --> 02:55.946
system was not tarnished. In 1995, during the 
session, I was also asked to work with the new

02:57.808 --> 03:05.355
president of Prairie View to help him become 
introduced and indoctrinated as to the Texas

03:06.078 --> 03:14.591
legislature. I proceeded to introduce him to a 
number of key members of the legislature,

03:14.611 --> 03:28.571
one of which was the local state representative 
from Bryan. The local representative was on the

03:28.591 --> 03:35.882
conference committee of the appropriations bill 
and immediately took an interest in the programs

03:36.503 --> 03:56.371
at Prairie View and asked Dr. Hines to put together 
a proposal on very short notice to provide a summer

03:36.503 --> 03:56.371
intern program for high school students that 
wished to attend Prairie View. They convinced the

03:57.973 --> 04:06.105
president we had very little time to do this and 
that the best way to do it was to do it with our

04:09.545 --> 04:14.811
video telecommunication system hookup between 
Austin and Prairie View. We went to the office,

04:16.192 --> 04:37.476
got on the system, and he was able to work a program 
up with his committee that was back on the campus in

04:16.192 --> 04:37.476
Prairie View, and in a very short time, a matter of 
hours, get a proposal to our local state

04:38.283 --> 04:47.555
representative who was able to get it in the 
appropriations bill. This kind of response is

04:49.518 --> 04:56.067
very important in working with the Texas 
legislature. There's very little time in a

04:57.989 --> 05:05.860
legislative session to respond and react to 
desires and wishes of the legislature. A

05:09.339 --> 05:24.342
particular program and funding was not something 
that the president of Prairie View was asking for,

05:09.339 --> 05:24.342
but it was kind of dropped in his lap, so to speak. 
There are good things that can happen during a

05:26.285 --> 05:31.493
legislative session. if a person is there and is 
alert and understands the process and knows what

05:33.228 --> 05:40.959
he's doing. No substitute, however, for turning 
out good students

05:42.921 --> 06:00.906
that the moms and dads will tell state legislators 
about and

06:02.557 --> 06:11.314
therefore leaving an image of doing your work back 
home, i.e. producing good students. It's to be a

06:13.980 --> 06:17.747
cultivation of all members. so that they will 
discuss issues with you freely and openly and even

06:18.689 --> 06:25.535
seek you out. And this is something that takes a lot 
of time and effort to cultivate the members

06:26.296 --> 06:41.570
because there's a constant rotation of new 
members coming into the legislature each

06:26.296 --> 06:41.570
session. There's been a strong believer in the use 
of our university presidents in addition to the

06:48.136 --> 06:53.121
people that work at the system level. These CEOs 
know their programs better than anyone and can

06:54.042 --> 07:03.651
present them to members of the legislature. It 
should be a coordinated effort in that the system

07:04.873 --> 07:15.443
officials should be kept notified of what is going 
on. There are conflicts between our system

07:16.958 --> 07:46.813
agencies and a system university, particularly 
Texas A&M University, but in each case these can be

07:16.958 --> 07:46.813
worked out and avoided if the interested parties 
are willing to work toward a compromise and let the

07:16.958 --> 07:46.813
system officials handle the issue. The image of 
Texas A&M University affects all components of

07:47.975 --> 07:57.409
the system and for many years has been looked upon 
as the system. Therefore, it's important that

07:58.370 --> 08:13.172
Texas A&M University's image be one of very 
highest regard as it reflects on everyone else.

